{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require dismissal of police for any misconduct and create new complaints body",
        "additional_details": "I think that public opinion in this matter is clear. I think that often justice is not served and police are too often allowed to continue to serve despite misconduct.\r\n \r\nWe want a one-strike policy for any incidents of misconduct and police to be investigated by totally independent bodies (not made up of previous police staff).\r\n \r\nFine with a reframe around mandatory dismissal of police officers found guilty of misconduct, and all complaints to be investigated by an independent body.\r\n",
        "background": "I think we need reform of how our complaints against and misconduct by police are handled, to protect the public first and foremost. I think the Government should require mandatory dismissal of all police found guilty of misconduct and all complaints should be investigated by an independent body.",
